<section id="sctWindowExtensionsDCO"><title>Extended Window Methods</title>
<indexterm><primary>dialog control object</primary><secondary>extended window methods</secondary></indexterm>
<para>
  The methods implemented by <xref linkend="clsWindowExtensions"/> class are listed in this
  section. The class name, <emphasis role="italic">WindowExtensions</emphasis> would seem to imply that the methods were
  common to all windows. However, the methods of this class are really just extensions to the original ooDialog
  framework, and many of the methods are not window specific methods.
</para>
<para>
  In many ways a lot of these methods do not make sense in the context of a dialog control. However, the methods have
  been dialog control methods for many years and must therefore remain dialog control methods for the sake of backwards
  compatibility. In almost all instances, the methods are best used in the context of a
  <xref linkend="chpDialogObject"/> object rather than a dialog control object.
</para>

